From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 16:11:12 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: skip applying scheme if region split for quota
 fails

The issue was discovered [1] by Sashiko.

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/20260718171523.87547-1-sj@kernel.org

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index 39ae6793794be..4c96d114ebc74 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -2953,7 +2953,8 @@ static void damos_apply_scheme(struct damon_ctx *c, struct damon_target *t,
 					c->min_region_sz);
 			if (!sz)
 				goto update_stat;
-			damon_split_region_at(t, r, sz);
+			if (damon_split_region_at(t, r, sz))
+				goto update_stat;
 		}
 		if (damos_core_filter_out(c, t, r, s))
 			return;
-- 
2.47.3

